&lt;p&gt;The Partnerships Analytics &amp;amp; Reporting Intern will support the Revenue Strategy &amp;amp; Operations team with data organization, reporting, insights, and recurring partner-facing or internal reporting needs. This role is intended for a candidate with interest in analytics, business intelligence, data organization, and storytelling through reporting. The candidate should also have a strong interest in exploring different verticals across the organization and be excited to gain exposure to the business side of sports, media, partnerships, events, and revenue operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support ongoing partnership, ticketing, merchandise, and media reporting needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help organize, clean, and structure data for internal and external reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with weekly and ad hoc reports across partner activity, inventory, revenue, and event performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support ticket reporting and merchandise reporting needs across key events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help translate raw data into clear summaries, tables, and topline insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with deck and slide formatting where reporting outputs need to be presented internally or externally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct weekly market research to support partnership strategy, prospecting, and category insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal tracking documents and reporting workflows to improve visibility across the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with general team tasks, and project support as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Potential Projects&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build or improve recurring merchandise reporting templates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with market research reports across priority categories, brands, or industries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support ticket reporting for key events, including the US Open.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with Digideck implementation, including content organization, asset uploads, and sales material updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Sponsor CX implementation by helping organize partner-facing materials, workflows, and internal tracking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help organize reporting inputs for partner recaps and commercial dashboards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help create streamlined reporting processes for recurring team use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideal Candidate Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interested in analytics, reporting, business operations, sports business, media, or partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with spreadsheets, data sets, and presentation materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented and organized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to identify patterns, summarize information clearly, and communicate insights simply.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable balancing recurring tasks with ad-hoc project-based work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Excel, Google Sheets, PowerPoint, Google Slides, or similar tools. Bonus if the candidate has previous experience in CRM tools such as Salesforce or SponsorCX.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter able to work independently while being a team player. Willingness to ask questions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Paid Summer Internship&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration:&lt;/strong&gt; 6–12 weeks, depending on timing of hire, business needs, and candidate availability. Start and end dates will remain flexible to account for college term schedules.&lt;/p&gt;
