&lt;p&gt;The Revenue Operations, Ad Ops &amp;amp; Partnerships Intern will support the Revenue Strategy &amp;amp; Operations team across a variety of operational, administrative, media, invoicing, and event-related workstreams. This role is intended for a highly organized generalist who is excited to gain exposure to the business side of sports, media, partnerships, events, and revenue operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support ad sales and media operations workstreams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with inventory management and tracking across available media, sponsorship, and commercial assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help with invoicing coordination, invoice tracking, and internal documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support deck formatting, slide cleanup, and presentation organization for internal and external materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with weekly market research across brands, categories, prospects, and industry trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help update media rights contract distribution lists and related tracking documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support organization and tracking of press releases and partner communication materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with general team coordination, administrative tasks, and project support as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Potential Projects&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support US Open onsite execution, partner support, and operational coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with Digideck implementation, including content organization, asset uploads, and sales material updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Sponsor CX implementation by helping organize partner-facing materials, workflows, and internal tracking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain ad sales inventory and media tracking documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain partners&#39; media plans on track, ensuring we are delivering in-full.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist team with Global media reports for past and present events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with invoice tracking and internal revenue operations documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the organization of partner materials, contracts, press releases, and distribution lists.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideal Candidate Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interested in sports business, media, partnerships, advertising, events, or revenue operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized, proactive, and comfortable jumping into a variety of tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to manage administrative and operational work with a positive, team-first attitude.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working across spreadsheets, decks, documents, and internal tracking systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communicator who can follow direction, ask smart questions, and keep projects moving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Excel, Google Sheets, PowerPoint, Google Slides, or similar tools preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with learning new systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Paid Summer Internship&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration:&lt;/strong&gt; 6–12 weeks, depending on timing of hire, business needs, and candidate availability. Start and end dates will remain flexible to account for college term schedules.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eligibility:&lt;/strong&gt; Candidates must be 18+ and legally eligible to work in the United States. Final eligibility requirements to be confirmed by HR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Academic Credit:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a paid internship and is not dependent on school credit. &lt;strong&gt;Hourly Rate&lt;/strong&gt;: $20.00/hr&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diversity creates a healthier atmosphere: equal opportunity employer M/F/D/V&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Senior Analyst will work in collaboration with other business units to understand key audience metrics for executive reporting, develop advanced analytics capabilities and drive strategic insight. The primary objective of the team is to grow the World Surf League (WSL)&amp;nbsp; fan base and spread our love of the sport and lifestyle of surfing around the world. This role will be based in WSL’s Los Angeles headquarters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect, organize, manage and report on WSL audience databases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage analytical tools and deliver insight on strategic initiatives through rigorous analysis and regular reporting to executive team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and forecast audience growth and engagement trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide data and audience insights to Sponsorship, Content and Events departments&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with multidisciplinary teams to drive outcomes on strategic projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create presentations for executive level communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee development, execution and analysis of audience surveys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with external vendors providing market research support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with analytics and digital teams to advance analytics capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Office tools, with significant expertise in Excel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong command of SQL and relational databases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Google Analytics, Big Query, YouTube Analytics, Facebook Insights and other digital analytics platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Digital audience growth and UI / UX optimization experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills (including slide writing)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to continuous improvement and professional development&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Existing experience in sports or entertainment sector a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for surfing and surf culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years work experience in a similar field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelors Degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Personal Attributes:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Above all, integrity and honesty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial; willingness to work independently with the best business practices in mind&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Masterful organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimism and energy for the brand and its future&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An open and collaborative nature&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A high degree of self-awareness of one’s own personal style, strengths and weaknesses and motivational triggers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intellectual curiosity and enthusiasm for learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Action Oriented—enjoys working hard and looks for challenges; works with urgency able to act and react as necessary, even if limited information is available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diversity creates a healthier atmosphere: equal opportunity employer M/F/D/V&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary Range: $100,000-$115,000 based on relevant experience&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Senior Manager, Global Business Development will be responsible for driving North America revenue growth, developing marquee partnerships, and cultivating new business opportunities across the WSL ecosystem — including events, media, content, digital platforms, and sustainability programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the SVP, Global Business Development, this individual will be involved in strategic prospecting, pitching, and closing of multi-dimensional partnerships that align with WSL’s brand values, audience, and long-term business strategy. The role is both highly entrepreneurial and deeply collaborative, requiring a strategic thinker and relationship builder who can translate brand needs into world-class, customized partnership solutions. This is a hybrid role, with 3 days in office based out of our Los Angeles headquarters.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities include (but not limited to):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnership Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a comprehensive understanding of WSL’s brand, products, audiences, and global positioning within the sports and entertainment ecosystem to articulate a unique and compelling commercial narrative.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, qualify, and secure new partners across our portfolio of events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create customized, year-round partnership programs that leverage WSL’s media, digital, event, and community assets in authentic, value-driven ways aligned with partner objectives to generate measurable ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorporate data and analytics to evaluate opportunities, forecast revenue potential, and optimize performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage a robust pipeline of prospective partners, maintaining disciplined tracking, forecasting, and reporting through CRM tools (Salesforce or similar).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration and Integration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with internal teams, including Marketing, Content, Broadcast, Digital, Athlete Relations, and Event Operations, to design innovative partnership platforms and deliver commercially sound, scalable solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal WSL teams to ensure sales strategy aligns with WSL’s brand purpose, creative vision, and organizational priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guarantee seamless transitions of new partners to the Marketing Partnerships team for activation and sustained success, ensuring continuity and excellent client service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance and Growth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently deliver annual sales growth objectives and contribute to long-term revenue planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a disciplined, transparent pipeline management process using CRM tools (e.g., Salesforce or similar) to track progress, forecast revenue, and report performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to special projects and cross-department initiatives that advance WSL’s broader commercial strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5+ years of experience in sports, entertainment, media, or brand partnership sales, with a proven record of securing six figure deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network of decision maker relationships across brands, agencies, and categories relevant to WSL’s ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
